  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a non‑stick skillet over medium heat and add a splash of sesame oil.",
    "In a bowl whisk the eggs, almond milk, mirin, salt, and baking powder until frothy.",
    "Stir in the coconut flour until the batter is smooth.",
    "Fold in the chopped pistachios.",
    "Pour the batter into the skillet, forming a thin, round pancake about 1 cm thick.",
    "Cook 3–4 minutes until the edges set, then flip and cook another 3 minutes until golden brown.",
    "Transfer the pancake to a plate, top with toasted sesame seeds and sliced scallions.",
    "Serve hot as a bowl, drizzle with a touch of soy sauce if desired."
